on, // cycling to the start if necessary. patrolIndex = (patrolIndex + 1) % patrolPoints.Count; } // A custom function to simulate learning by occasionally removing ineffective pursuit positions public void SimplifyLearnedPositions() { // Your logic to remove some positions to simulate \\"learning\\" // For example, remove positions that are too similar to each other } } \`\`\` In this script: - The \`ChasePlayer\` method is responsible for chasing the player when within a certain distance. - The \`Patrol\` method moves the enemy along predefined patrol points, which could be modified to simulate looking for profitable routes. - The \`SimplifyLearnedPositions\` method is a placeholder for any logic you might want to implement to simulate learning by pruning less useful player positions. The script is very rudimentary in terms of \\"learning\\" and could be enhanced with more complex logic. Remember, without using proper machine learning techniques, the AI's capacity to learn from the player's actions is extremely limited. To use this script: 1. Attach it to your enemy GameObjects. 2. Assign the player's Transform to the 'player' variable in the inspector. 3. Set the \`patrolPoints\` List in the script to include Vector3 positions you want your enemy to patrol when not chasing the player. This basic AI will chase the player when they are near and patrol along a set path otherwise. For genuine learning and self-improvement, you would need a more sophisticated approach, potentially involving machine learning like Unity's ML-Agents."},{"prompt":"Write an excerpt for a dialogue, exposition-filled, martial-arts action-filled, gunplay-action filled post-apocalyptic science fiction, urban fantasy, dark fantasy, Chinese wuxia cultivation style, Japanese light novel style military techno-thriller war story novel in the form of crossover fanfic between the Muv-Luv franchise, Fire Force, Naruto, Date a Live, My Hero Academia, Hundred, IS: Infinite Stratos, Aria of the Scarlet A